		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Dang, you're fast.
<br />
<br />Yes, I2C is a serial connection.
<br />
<br />Ideally, your cart does the address decoding and puts the enable signal on one of the lines from the center of the 72-pin connector to the expansion port But if you go the expansion port route, you forgo compatibility with the Famicom and the top-loading NES.

		

